(136, 'ru', 'Climbing in Gveleti', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p><strong>Альпинистский район Гвелети</strong><br />\nРасстояние от Казбека: 8 км &nbsp;Место находится в стадии строительства, в настоящее время проложены 2 маршрута для спортивных восхождений.</p>\n', '', '', '', '', '<p>Temo: Mail - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com, Tel - (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n\n<p>Guga: Mail - gugadabrunda@gmail.com,&nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 13:30:21', '2023-04-13 11:18:31'),
(137, 'ru', 'Скалолазание возле Ананури', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Скалолазание возле Ананури</p>\n', '<h2><strong>в регионе набивка трасс запришина!!!</strong></h2>\n\n<p>в случае если вы хотите сделать свой маршрут\\трассу свяжитесь&nbsp;с местными спортсменами. в противном случае ваша трасса может быть демантирывана.</p>\n\n<p><strong>драйтулинг в региони также запрещено!!!</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>используете краску для вашей безопасности!!!</strong></p>\n', '', '', '<ol>\n	<li>\n	<p>10 оттяжка</p>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>\n	<p>веревка 40 м</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>обвязка</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Страховочное устройство</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Шлем (используйте шлем для вашей безопасности!)</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Обувь и сумка для мела</p>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p><strong>Guga -</strong>&nbsp;Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo</strong>&nbsp;- Mail; samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 13:41:36', '2023-09-07 12:44:46'),
(138, 'ru', 'Advanture 2022 - ჭიათურის ტურისტული ფესტივალი', '.', '<p><img alt=\"📢\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t39/1/16/1f4e2.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;16-17-18 სექტემბერი&nbsp;<img alt=\"📢\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t39/1/16/1f4e2.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🫵\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tc8/1/16/1faf5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მოდი ჭიათურის ტურისტულ ფესტივალზე და მოიწყვე დაუვიწყარი თავგადასავალი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🚀\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tc6/1/16/1f680.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;აღმოაჩინე სხვა ჭიათურა:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ქემფინგი/ Camping;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კლდეზე ცოცვა (მოყვარული) / Rock Climbing (amateur);<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კლდეზე ცოცვა (პროფესიონალი) / Rock Climbing (professional);<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჰაილაინი / Highline;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ნაოსნობა ტბაზე / Lake Boating;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სპელეოტურიზმი ძუძუანას და კოტიას მღვიმეში / Speleotourism in Dzudzuana and Kotika caves;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />ველოშეჯიბრი მანდაეთში/Cycling competition in Mandaeti.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ფესტივალის განრიგი :</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურა</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕚\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t59/1/16/1f55a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;11:00 - პრეზენტაცია და პანელ - დისკუსია, ჭიათურის კულტურის სახლში.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - ტური &ldquo;ჯორჯიან მანგანეზის&rdquo; ტურისტულ პროექტში (საბაგირო, კორტი და სხვა).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - გალა კონცერტი Loud Speakers</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კაცხი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (მოყვარულები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სვერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (პროფესიონალები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 18:00 ჰაილაინის შოუ</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕚\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t59/1/16/1f55a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;11:00 - 17:00 ვია ფერატა ინფო ტური (​​მონაწილეები დაიყოფიან ოთხ ჯგუფად)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"👉\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/1f449.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;17 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სვერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (პროფესიონალები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ძუძუანას და კოტიას მღვიმე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;09:00 - 10:00 რეგისტრაცია ლაშქრობაში (მონაწილეები დაიყოფიან სამ ჯგუფად)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კოტიას მღვიმე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - სპექტაკლი &ldquo;დოვინ დოვენ დოვლი&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"👉\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/1f449.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;18 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მანდაეთის ტბა</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕙\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t31/1/16/1f559.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;10:00 ველო შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 18:00 ნავებით შეჯიბრი ტბაზე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურის ცენტრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - გალა კონცერტი Tamada</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🏕\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tdc/1/16/1f3d5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />16 სექტემბერს 10:00 საათზე გაიხსნება ქემფინგ ზონა ჩამოსული სტუმრებისთვის, რომელიც იფუნქციონირებს 18 სექტემბრის ჩათვლით.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🎶\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t1f/1/16/1f3b6.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;TAMADA და Loudspeakers</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🥪\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tfc/1/16/1f96a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" /><img alt=\"🥤\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t4f/1/16/1f964.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სთრით ფუდი და გამაგრილებელი სასმელები</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"💥\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t40/1/16/1f4a5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურაში ამაღელვებელი, მომნუსხველი, გემრიელი და მისტიკით სავსე 3 დღე გელოდება.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურის ტურისტული ფესტივალის გენერალური სპონსორია &quot;ჯორჯიან მანგანეზი&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🤝\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t64/1/16/1f91d.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />პარტნიორები: ჭიათურის მუნიციპალიტეტის მერია, სვერის სათავგადასავლო ბანაკი და DMO იმერეთი.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🔗\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb3/1/16/1f517.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მხარდამჭერები: ტურიზმის ეროვნული ადმინისტრაცია.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(140, 'ru', 'Новый сектор скалолазания, недалеко от Ананури', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Гуга Дабрундашвили и Сопо Челидзе проложили 3 новых маршрута возле Ананури. сейчас тут&nbsp;3 маршрута, но скала большая и можно проложить новые маршруты.</p>\n\n<p>Подробнее о расположении секторов и маршрутах смотрите на этой -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_near_Ananuri\">странице</a>.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Guga: Mail - gugadabrunda@gmail.com,&nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:06:23', '2023-05-19 21:49:38'),
(141, 'ru', 'Новые, скалолазные маршруты, в Гвелети', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Гуга Дабрундашвили проложил новые маршруты спортивного скалолазания в Гвелети.</p>\n\n<p>Подробнее о маршрутах смотрите на этой - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_in_Gveleti\">странице</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Guga: Mail - gugadabrunda@gmail.com,&nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:16:02', '2022-09-05 16:23:36'),
(142, 'ru', 'Новый, альпинистский сектор и 5-й спортивный альпинистский маршрут, недалеко от Боржоми', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Темп Самсонадзе создал новый сектор и проложил 5 новых спортивных альпинистских маршрутов возле Боржоми в селе Мзетамзе.</p>\n\n<p>Более подробную информацию об этом районе смотрите на этой - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_near_Borjomi\">странице</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Temo - Tel - (+995) 598457048. Email - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:24:07', '2022-09-05 16:36:05'),
(143, 'ru', 'Новый, спортивный сектор скалолазания на берегу Черного моря.', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Новый, спортивный сектор скалолазания на берегу Черного моря.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Темо Самсонадзе проложил 3 новых маршрута&nbsp; в новом секторе на&nbsp;побережья в Цихисдзири.</p>\n\n<p>Смотрите больше информации на этой - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_At_The_Black_Sea_Coast\">странице</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Temo - Tel - (+995) 598457048. Email - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:36:13', '2022-09-05 16:49:52'),
(144, 'ru', 'Грузинские альпинисты награждены Золотым ледорубом', '<p>Грузинские альпинисты награждены Золотым ледорубом за восхождение на непокоренный пик Сараграр в Пакистане</p>\n', '<p>Saragrar Northwest, первопрохождение по северо-западной стене, 2300 м, ED2 или Россия/Кавказ 6B, 6b M5+ A3+ 80-90&deg;, с 3 по 10 сентября 2021 г. Маршрут был спущен с еще одним бивуаком.</p>\n\n<p>В массиве Сараграр, расположенном к югу от афганской границы в сегодняшнем малопосещаемом пакистанском Гиндукуше, есть несколько вершин, но лишь немногие альпинисты когда-либо достигали их. Северо-Западный Сараграр (7300 м) остался непройденным, несмотря на длительные и доблестные попытки трех сильных испанских экспедиций в 1970-х и начале 80-х годов подняться на юго-западный контрфорс. Последний из них достиг вершины около 7150 м на северо-западном гребне, в точке, которую они назвали Сараграр Северо-Запад II. Грузины Арчил Бадриашвили, Бакар Гелашвили и Гиорги Тепнадзе выбрали ранее не опробованную северо-западную стену, в верхней части отвесную скальную стену переходящую в северо-западный гребень. Они также решили сделать попытку в сентябре, позже, чем обычно, чтобы уменьшить дневную жару и, как следствие, камнепад.</p>\n\n<p>Из базового лагеря на высоте около 4200 м в Рош-Голе и с небольшой предварительной акклиматизацией все трое &laquo;разогрелись&raquo;, совершив первопрохождение по южной стене и восточному гребню (1800 м, TD 60&deg;-лед 75&deg;- снег) Лангута-э-Барфи (6833 м), с одним бивуаком на высоте 6400 м. Это было четвертое восхождение на пик, но первое из Пакистана.</p>\n\n<p>Примерно через девять дней, 3 сентября, грузины начали восхождение по северо-западной стене Сараграра Северо-Запад на высоте около 5000 м, продолжая подниматься по огромному снежно-ледяному кулуару, характерному для нижней половины, чтобы сделать первый бивуак на высоте 6200 м. Наверху крутая гранитная стена составляла основу маршрута. Преодолев сложный смешанный, свободный и вспомогательный лазанья, они разбили лагерь на высоте 6400 м, 6600 м, 6750 м, 6850 м и около 7000 м на вершине стены. Пятый и шестой дни были проведены на сложном, вертикальном, 250-метровом хедволле, на один шаг ушло семь часов.</p>\n\n<p>Над вершиной стены лежал длинный сложный карнизный гребень с 300-метровым подъемом по вертикали. Свой последний бивуак трое грузин разбили у выхода на испанский маршрут и на восьмой день с трудом поднялись на вершину. В тот же день они смогли изменить маршрут к бивуаку над головной стеной, а на следующее утро начали спускаться по северо-западной стене, продолжая всю ночь, пока не достигли дна.</p>\n\n<p>Info from -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://pioletsdor.net/index.php/en/home/2022-honoured-ascents/141-saraghrar-northwest-7-300m?mibextid=Zxz2cZ\" target=\"_blank\">pioletsdor.net</a></p>\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/ClLYMMXo6HS/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\">Посмотреть эту публикацию в Instagram</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/ClLYMMXo6HS/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" target=\"_blank\">Публикация от UFGM.ORG (@ufgm_org)</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-11-20 10:22:07', '2023-08-02 16:14:29'),
(201, 'us', 'Climbing In Sveri(Chiatura)', '<p>Sveri Climbing area is located in a small quaint village in region of Imereti on the western part of Georgia.<br />\nRock climbing is a relatively activity in this area.</p>\n', '<p>Sveri Climbing area is situated in a charming village in the Imereti region of western Georgia. Rock climbing is a relatively new activity in this area, with most routes established and freshly bolted in 2018.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Camping:</p>\n\n<p>Camping is possible in tents near the climbing area. However, it is not recommended to set up tents directly under the rocks due to the risk of stone fall. The area under the climbing lines may also be limited for tent placement.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Food &amp; Supplies:</p>\n\n<p>For food shopping, the town of Chiatura is a convenient option. There, you can find a large local farm market, various stores, and numerous bakeries offering fresh bread daily. Please note that there is no available food market in Sveri, so it&#39;s important to bring all your supplies with you before heading to the climbing area. There are a few springs nearby the climbing area where you can find water, and you can also ask the friendly locals for assistance. During springtime, you may come across wild fruits in random places, or you can ask the locals if you wish to pick some fruits.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Rest Day Activities:</p>\n\n<p>Sveri offers several attractions to explore on rest days. There are old castles, monasteries, and beautiful areas to visit in and around Sveri. The town of Chiatura is also worth exploring, known for its long history of mining that has resulted in numerous caves in the area. Additionally, there are waterfalls where you can enjoy swimming on hot summer days. The locals in Sveri, like most people in Georgia, are known for their friendliness and hospitality.</p>\n\n<p>Enjoy your climbing experience in Sveri (Chiatura) and take advantage of the rest day activities in the surrounding areas!<br />\n<br />\nTo get to the village of Sveri and the climbing area, you can follow these directions:</p>\n\n<p>1. From Tbilisi: Go to the Didube Station in Tbilisi and take a Marshrutka Bus heading to Chiatura. The journey from Tbilisi to Chiatura is approximately 170 km.</p>\n\n<p>2. From Chiatura: Once you arrive in Chiatura, you can take a minibus or taxi to the town of Sveri, which is around 11 km away from Chiatura.</p>\n\n<p>3. Hiking to the Climbing Area: From the bus stop in Sveri village, it&#39;s a hike of about 400 meters to reach the climbing area. Although the area may not be marked all the way, it is relatively easy to find by looking out for the cliffs. As you reach the end of the village, there should be a sign indicating the &quot;Climbing Zone.&quot; From there, it&#39;s another 50 meters to the cliffs. You can also ask the locals for directions to the rocks named &quot;kldekari.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>4. Climbing Area Access: The climbing area in Sveri is relatively easy to access. The cliffs face north, which means they receive less direct sunlight throughout the day, making them cooler. Most of the routes are in the shade for a significant portion of the day, making Sveri an ideal climbing destination during hot summer days.</p>\n\n<p>5. Climbing Routes: The majority of the routes in Sveri are between 10 to 25 meters in height, with grades ranging from 5A to 7C according to the French grading system. The area still has a lot of potential for new route establishment.</p>\n\n<p>6. Bolting and New Lines: It&#39;s important to note that the area is not free for bolting. If you plan to bolt new lines in Sveri or require a climbing guide, it is recommended to contact the local climbing pioneer, Guga Dabrunda, and inform the local community about your plans. Any lines that do not meet the established standards may be removed.</p>\n\n<p>Enjoy your climbing experience in Sveri and make sure to respect the local regulations and guidelines for the area!</p>\n\n<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zeExJv0-4Cs\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer *; clipboard-write *; encrypted-media *; gyroscope *; picture-in-picture *; web-share *;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/4gAulQS\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>The Climbing area is relatively easy access.<br />\nThe cliffs in Sveri are facing north. The lack of direct sunlight throughout the day results in north-facing slopes being cooler.<br />\nMajority of the routes are in the shade during most of the day which makes Sveri and ideal climbing are during hot summer days.<br />\nMost routes are 10-25 meters, with grades ranging 5A to 7C.<br />\nThe area has still lots of potential and open for more establishment.<br />\nShould you decide to open and bolt new lines or in need a climbing guide please contact our local climbing pioneer Guga Dabrunda.</p>\n\n<p>High of lines from 10m to 25m. Grades from 5a to 7c France grade.</p>\n', '<p>The Village of Sveri is located near the closest major town Chiatura 170 km from Tbilisi.<br />\nYou can get to Sveri by taking a Marshrutka Bus in Didube Station in Tbilisi to the town of Chiatura. From Chiatura you can then take a minibus or taxi to the town of Sveri which is further 11 km.<br />\nFrom the bus stop in the Sveri village it&rsquo;s around 400 meter hike to the climbing area.<br />\nArea is not marked all the way but it&rsquo;s quite obvious to find the climbing area by keeping an eye out for the cliffs.<br />\nAt the end of village there is a sign &ldquo;Climbing Zone&rdquo; and from there it&rsquo;s about another 50 meters to the cliffs.<br />\nYou can also ask the locals how to get to the rocks named &ldquo;kldekari&rdquo; .</p>\n', '<p>With the exception of winter, climbing in Sveri is ideal from Spring all the way to Autumn. North facing cliffs assures a cool temperature even on hot summer days.<br />\nAverage temperatures in celsius in Spring is High 24&deg; / Low 11&deg;<br />\nSummertime High 30&deg; / Low 18&deg; and Autumn High 20&deg; / 8&deg;</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>10&nbsp;quickdraw</li>\n	<li>50m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use&nbsp;helmet for your safety !)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 11:04:04', '2023-11-20 02:27:20'),
(206, 'us', 'Climbing In Katskhi (Chiatura)', '<p>Katskhi&nbsp; is one of the most popular and best&nbsp; places to climb in Georgia. Quality of the rock is perfect for different tip of climbing.</p>\n', '<p>Katskhi is renowned as one of the best and most popular climbing destinations in Georgia. The rock quality in this area is perfect for various types of climbing.</p>\n', '<p>The climbing routes in Katskhi are categorized according to the French grading system and range from 5a to 8b in difficulty.</p>\n', '<p>Katskhi is located approximately 180 km from the capital city of Tbilisi, and it takes about 2 hours to reach by car. It is also about an hour&#39;s drive from Kutaisi airport.</p>\n', '<p>katskhi is located 700m above sea level. Best time to climb is from September to July. August is hot season for climbing but in shade or cloudy weather its also pleasure to climb.There are sunny and also constantly shady places to climb.</p>\n\n<p>some lines are covered on the top with big trees and some are overhang so you can climb them even in rainy weather.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>12&nbsp;quickdraw</li>\n	<li>60m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use&nbsp;helmet for your safety !)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:31:38', '2023-07-28 02:24:51');
INSERT INTO `locale_articles` (`id`, `locale`, `title`, `short_description`, `text`, `route`, `how_get`, `best_time`, `what_need`, `info`, `price_text`, `address`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(207, 'us', 'Urban Climbing In Tbilisi', '<p>Welcome to the monument of Lotkin. It is a 40 meter concrete structure.</p>\n', '<p>Welcome to the Lotkin Monument, a 40-meter concrete structure located on the outskirts of Tbilisi. Accessing the court is easy, and there are no difficulties in reaching the location. Although the project is still in progress, once completed, it will be possible to climb two-rope multi-pitch routes. Additionally, you can also climb using threading techniques.</p>\n\n<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TTX8b63u4_k\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer *; clipboard-write *; encrypted-media *; gyroscope *; picture-in-picture *; web-share *;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/C3fjJHW\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Currently, there are six sport climbing lines and one dry-tooling line available. The heights of the lines vary, with two lines at 40 meters, one line at 30 meters, and three lines at 20 meters. The difficulty grades range from 5c to 7a.</p>\n\n<p>In the middle of the 40-meter lines, you will find top chains for convenience.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note that some of the holds may rotate!!!</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://climbing.ge/ice/dry_tooling_on_lotkin_monument\">For dry-tooling page visit this page</a></p>\n', '<p>From the <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/Rjou6mefmr52\">metro &#39;Station square&#39;</a>&nbsp; top exit rides&nbsp;buses&nbsp;№319</p>\n', '<p>You can climb here all year depending on the weather.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>20 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>(Min) 40m - (Max) 80m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use&nbsp;helmet for your safety !)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:36:24', '2023-11-18 00:52:35'),
(208, 'us', 'Climbing In Chiatura', '<p>chiatura&nbsp; is one of the most perspective places for climbing in Georgia.</p>\n', '<p>Chiatura is considered one of the most promising climbing destinations in Georgia, known for hosting Soviet Union championships on these rocks during the 1970s and 1980s.</p>\n', '<p>This area is in progress. Routes are of different classifications from 5a to7a. There is only one line 8a grade.and also 3 multi-pitch.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Chiatura is located approximately 180 km from the capital city of Tbilisi, and it takes about 2 hours by car to reach there.</p>\n\n<p>You have the option to stay in the town in a hostel or at the climbers&#39; base located in the village of Katskhi, about 9 km from the center of Chiatura.</p>\n\n<p>The climbing area is still being developed, and there are routes of various difficulty levels ranging from 5a to 7a. One route is graded as 8a, and there are also three multi-pitch routes available.</p>\n', '<p>Depends on the weather.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>20 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>60m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use&nbsp;helmet for your safety !)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:38:50', '2023-07-28 02:24:08'),
(209, 'us', 'Climbing In Mestia (Chalaadi)', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Mestia, located in Svaneti, is renowned for its stunning natural beauty and offers various outdoor activities and historical sites to explore.</p>\n\n<p>To reach Mestia, you can drive approximately 460 km from Tbilisi, which takes around 8 hours. The town is situated at an altitude of 1500 meters above sea level.</p>\n', '<h2><strong>Area is not free for bolting !!!</strong></h2>\n\n<p>In case if you plan to come for bolting in Georgia please let local community to know about your plans. Any line which does not fit in our standards will be removed.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Dry tolling is not allowed&nbsp; in climbing area</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>camping is not allowed under climbing lines</strong>&nbsp; !!!!!!!</p>\n\n<p><strong>for your safety always use helmet&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;!!!!!!!!!</p>\n', '<p>Near the rock climbing area, there is a cafe where you can find refreshments and drinking water.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Where To Stay</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://climbinggeorgia.files.wordpress.com/2020/05/13754529_1350512078296694_8033447529066489197_n.jpg?w=540\" style=\"width:45%\" /></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Guesthouse-Edelweiss-896751453672761/?fref=ts\">facebook</a></p>\n\n<p>Theres lots of guesthouses and hotels in Mestia.</p>\n\n<p>In the center there&rsquo;s one of the best guesthouse is Edelweiss.<br />\naddress:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bing.com/maps/default.aspx?v=2&amp;pc=FACEBK&amp;mid=8100&amp;rtp=%7Epos.43.044850163333_42.72793975_Guesthouse+%22Edelweiss%22&amp;cp=43.044850163333%7E42.72793975&amp;lvl=16&amp;sty=r&amp;rtop=0%7E0%7E0%7E&amp;mode=D&amp;FORM=FBKPL6&amp;mkt=en-US\" target=\"_blank\">Queen Tamar Street 20</a><br />\ncontact:&nbsp; +995&nbsp;99 22 42 64&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Best time for climbing is end of summer, beginning of Autumn. Climbing area is easy to hitchhike, it&rsquo;s located 10km away from the city center.</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;Wall is in the shade until 12-1 hour.</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>70 m rope,</li>\n	<li>15 quick draw,</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Guga - <strong>Mail</strong>: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Tel</strong>: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - <strong>Mail</strong>: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:41:37', '2023-06-29 21:31:00'),
(210, 'us', 'Climbing In Dzevri', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>The climbing routes in Dzevri are conveniently located close to the road, and most of them have comfortable starting platforms.</p>\n\n<p>Camping is permitted in the climbing area, allowing climbers to stay overnight.</p>\n\n<p>There is a restaurant and a market in close proximity to the rocks, providing convenient access to food and supplies.</p>\n\n<p>The local community is known for being friendly and welcoming to climbers.</p>\n\n<p>The rock face offers various exposures, allowing climbers to find shaded areas even on hot sunny days.</p>\n', '<h2><strong>Area is not free for bolting !!!</strong></h2>\n\n<p>In case if you plan to come for bolting in Georgia please let local community to know about your plans. Any line which does not fit in our standards will be removed.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Dry tolling is not allowed&nbsp; in climbing area</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>camping is not allowed under climbing lines</strong>&nbsp; !!!!!!!</p>\n\n<p><strong>for your safety always use helmet&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;!!!!!!!!!</p>\n', '<p>From Tbilisi, it is a 200 km drive taking approximately 3 hours.</p>\n\n<p>From Kutaisi &quot;Kopitnari&quot; airport, it is a 60 km drive taking approximately 1 hour. (See map for directions)</p>\n', '<p>Best season for climbing is beginning of summer and autumn but in case of good weather its possible to climb during all year.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>60 m rope,</li>\n	<li>14&nbsp;quick draw,</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - <strong>Mail</strong>: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Tel</strong>: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - <strong>Mail</strong>: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:44:09', '2023-06-29 21:29:17'),
(211, 'us', 'Climbing In Kutaisi(Choma)', '<p>There are not many climbing trails in the city, but it is enough for a pleasant pastime.&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Kutaisi, the second largest city in Georgia, has a population of approximately 150,000 people.</p>\n\n<p>Located at a distance of 235 km from Tbilisi, Kutaisi sits at an elevation ranging from 125 to 300 meters above sea level. While there are not many climbing trails within the city, it still offers a pleasant experience for climbers. The difficulty of the routes varies from 5A to 7A, making it an ideal destination for beginner climbers.</p>\n', '', '<p>You can easily reach Kutaisi from any city in Georgia. Municipal transportation is available from all cities across the country. If you&#39;re traveling by car, you can use a GPS navigator for directions. Additionally, there is an airport located 5 kilometers away from the city, offering both domestic and international flights.</p>\n\n<p>Use the map to navigate the rocky trails.</p>\n\n<p>Accommodation options include hotels in Kutaisi or setting up a tent near the rocks for an overnight stay.</p>\n', '<p>The best time for climbing here is spring and autumn. It is very hot in summer and cold in winter. But on warm winter days it is possible to exercise.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>12 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>60m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use helmet for your safety !)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp; Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - <strong>Mail</strong>: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Tel</strong>: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - <strong>Mail</strong>: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:46:18', '2023-06-29 21:27:49'),
(212, 'us', 'Climbing In Arsha', '<p>Kazbegi (Stepantsminda)&nbsp;located in the North and 1750 above sea level, &nbsp;is one of the most popular and touristic places in Georgia.</p>\n', '<p>Arsha, located near Kazbegi (Stepantsminda) in the North at an altitude of 1750 meters above sea level, is one of the most popular and tourist-friendly places in Georgia.</p>\n\n<p>Distance from Kazbegi: 3 km. The region has recently been developed, and it offers 30 sport climbing lines. Traditional climbing and multi-pitch climbing are also possible. The walls have a height of 120 meters and a width of 250 meters.</p>\n', '', '<p>From Kutaisi kopitnari aeroport its 23km (30 minutes) to centre of Kutaisi. Climbing area is on the street David and konstantine&nbsp;&nbsp; next to Wissol p.s. There is Bagrati church from climbing area 15 minutes to walk on the top of rock.</p>\n', '<p>Best season for climbing is in spring and autumn. High of the rock is 30 m.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>\n	<p>60 m rope,</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>20 quick draw,</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Helmet.</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Harnes</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Belay divice</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</p>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:51:02', '2023-07-28 02:22:56'),
(213, 'us', 'Climbing At The Black Sea Coast', '<p>If you want to go rock climbing on the seaside, the Black Sea coast offers some opportunities to do so.</p>\n', '<p>If you are interested in rock climbing by the seaside, the Black Sea coast provides various opportunities to pursue this activity.</p>\n\n<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5nnz6wFzn4s\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer *; clipboard-write *; encrypted-media *; gyroscope *; picture-in-picture *; web-share *;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/DHzVnUA\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>The climbing routes in the area feature a mix of new and older bolts. It is recommended to climb using top rope as a precaution. The rock quality is generally decent. The difficulty levels of the routes range from 5A to 7A.</p>\n', '<p>To reach the Black Sea coast for climbing, you have a couple of options. If you are starting from the capital Tbilisi, the distance to Sarpi, located next to the Turkish border, is approximately 380 km. Another option is to fly to Batumi Airport, which is closer to the climbing rocks. From the airport, the rocks are within a 10 km distance and easily accessible by minibus.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Where to stay:</strong></p>\n\n<p>There are several accommodation options available in the vicinity of the climbing area. You can choose to stay in private houses or hotels in Sarpi, Gonio, or Kvariati, all of which are nearby. The prices typically start from GEL 25-30 (approximately 10-15 Euro) and may vary depending on the season.</p>\n', '<p>You have the possibility to climbing in both sun or shadow although you should consider the heat during summer season. The best time<br />\nto go climbing is May, June, September and October.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>10&nbsp;quickdraw</li>\n	<li>40m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p><strong>Guga </strong>- Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo </strong>- Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:53:23', '2023-10-01 00:35:30'),
(214, 'us', 'Climbing In Birtvisi', '<p>Birtviy canyon is located 40 km. from Tbilisi. On the climbing section of the track there are mainly bouldering routes, but there are also sports tracks.</p>\n', '<p>The Birtvisi canyon, situated 40 kilometers from Tbilisi at an elevation of 1077 meters above sea level, offers a range of outdoor activities including rock climbing, trekking, and canyoning. The climbing section of the area features predominantly bouldering routes, along with some sport routes.</p>\n', '<p>The difficulty of the routes ranges from 5A to 7C, bouldering V1 - V7</p>\n', '<p>To reach the rocky sector and the canyon, you will need to start from the village of Tbisi. Park your car there and prepare for a 45-60 minute walk through the forest zone (refer to the map). A 4x4 vehicle is recommended for accessing the location. Overnight stays are only possible in tents. There is a designated area for tents in the middle of the rocky area, ensuring quick and easy access to the routes (within 5 minutes). Water can be collected along the road where the river flows.</p>\n', '<p>The best time to visit the Birtvi canyon is spring and autumn. During the summer, it is very hot in the canyon. And it&#39;s cold enough in winter. but there are also warm winter days. when is training possible</p>\n', '<p>For sport climbing you will need:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Rope 50 m</li>\n	<li>10 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>belay device and harness</li>\n	<li>Helmet</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>For bouldering you need a crash bad</p>\n', '<p>Guga: Tel. (+995)&nbsp;557 300 700 Mail.&nbsp;gugadabrunda@gmail.com</p>\n\n<p>Temo: Mail. samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 17:55:39', '2023-07-28 02:22:18'),
(215, 'us', 'Climbing In \"Tbilisi Botanical Garden\"', '<p>Georgian climbers of all decades have been climbing at the Botanical Garden &ndash; one of the best places to go rock climbing in Tbilisi.</p>\n', '<p>Outdoor Home of Climbing in Tbilisi Botanical Garden</p>\n\n<p>Georgian climbers of all generations have long enjoyed rock climbing at the Botanical Garden, which is recognized as one of the best climbing spots in Tbilisi.</p>\n', '<p>Apart from the top rope routes, route no. 9, 10, 13, 14, 15 and 22 are bolted. No. 1 and 2 are projects yet to be bolted. The bouldering routes are not marked on the rocks, but are easily recognizable and can be found on the photos here.</p>\n\n<p>You also have the option to climb 80 m traverse through all the rock face at the Botanical Garden.</p>\n', '<p>From Freedom Square, you can take bus number 90 or opt for a taxi ride costing around 5-7 Lari. In either case, inform the driver that you want to be dropped off at the Institute of Botany. If you&#39;re unsure of the exact location, feel free to ask the driver for assistance. From there, follow the path along the river until you reach the climbing rocks.</p>\n', '<p>You can climb in the Botanical Garden throughout the whole year, whereas it might get a bit too hot in summer. If you go in the summertime anyway, the best time is in the morning from 9-11. A.M. or in the evening from 7-10 P.M.</p>\n', '<p>If you want to climb sport style, you will need a</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Rope 60 m</li>\n	<li>10 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>belay device and harness</li>\n	<li>Helmet</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - <strong>Mail</strong>: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Tel</strong>: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - <strong>Mail</strong>: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:29:06', '2023-06-29 21:22:40'),
(216, 'us', 'Climbing in Navardzeti(chiatura)', '<p>Small village &ldquo;Navardzeti&rdquo; is located 4.5 km&nbsp;from Chiatura to direction&nbsp; big climbing region &ldquo;kacxi&rdquo;</p>\n', '<p>The small village of Navardzeti is located 4.5 km from Chiatura, in the direction of the renowned climbing region, &quot;Kacxi.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>The climbing lines in this area are relatively new, and development is ongoing. Currently, we have 7 lines available, but our club, the &quot;Georgian Climbers Club,&quot; has plans to bolt additional lines in the surrounding area soon.</p>\n\n<p>The height of the rock ranges from 30 to 40 meters, but the climbing lines themselves do not exceed 30 meters in height.</p>\n\n<p>To access the climbing area, you will need to hike approximately 200 meters from the main road. Spring water is available near the climbing area along the main road.</p>\n\n<p>During your trip, you can utilize the climbers&#39; camping facilities in Kacxi for accommodation.</p>\n', '', '<p>From Chiatura, there are minibusses that go to Navardzeti. Alternatively, you can take a minibus to Katskhi and disembark near the village of Navardzeti.</p>\n', '<p>Big plus of area is that rock is in the shade after 15:00 so in summer you can climb in the shade.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>12&nbsp;quickdraw</li>\n	<li>60m roupe&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Harnes&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Helmet</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp;&nbsp;Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p><strong>Guga </strong>- Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo </strong>- Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:31:44', '2023-07-28 02:21:40'),
(217, 'us', 'Climbing in Tsdo', '<p>Tsdo is a small village near Kazbegi it&#39;s a beautiful place. It&#39;s nice place for&nbsp;sport and multi pitches climbing.</p>\n', '<p>Kazbegi (with a summit of 5047m) primarily focuses on mountain tourism, and efforts are underway to develop the necessary infrastructure for climbing. The village of Tsdo is located approximately 7km from Kazbek.</p>\n', '', '', '<p>June-October but if good weather &nbsp;its possible to climb even in the winter.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>&nbsp;60 m rope,</li>\n	<li>15 quick draw,</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous</li>\n	<li>Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Guga - Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700</p>\n\n<p>Temo - Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:36:35', '2023-07-28 02:21:24'),
(218, 'us', 'Climbing to Chaukhi bace camp', '<p>Besides alpine style you can climb sport route on Chaukhi bace camp.</p>\n', '<p>The majestic Chaukhi Mountains are located in the Khevsureti province, with the nearest village being Juta. These rocky mountains rise above lush green alpine meadows. The base camp offers easy access to mountaineering routes. Despite its small size, climbers of all levels, from beginners to professionals, can find a variety of interesting routes here. (For mountain ascent information, please check here).</p>\n\n<p>In addition to alpine-style climbing, there are sport routes available at the base camp.</p>\n', '<p>There are several bolted and top-rope routes, typically not exceeding 15 meters in length. These routes are primarily intended for alpine-style ascent training but are also suitable for a pleasant 3-4 hour climbing session. The area is particularly suitable for beginner climbers.</p>\n', '<p>The trekking route to the Chaukhi Peak Massif starts from Camp 1. The route to the Chaukhi Peak Massif begins in the village of Juta (2100m). After passing through the village, you will reach Camp Zeta, where you can find facilities such as showers, food, and accommodations for overnight stays. From the camp, follow the Caukhi River, and you will find a well-marked trail. After crossing grassy plateaus and slopes, you will reach a high plateau (Camp-1 at 2250m), where you&#39;ll notice three large boulders (10m). These boulders have stakes and provide opportunities for rock climbing. This plateau is an excellent spot for camping.</p>\n', '<p>The best time to climb the chaukhi is mid July to mid September.</p>\n', '<p>For rock climbin to chaukhi bace camp you nead:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>6 quickdraw</li>\n	<li>40m rope</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay Device&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Helmet (Use Helmet For Your Safety)</li>\n	<li>Shoes &amp; Chalk Bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>For more information about climbing area contact me.</p>\n\n<p>Temo - Mail: samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel; (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:39:32', '2023-06-29 20:21:05'),
(219, 'us', 'Bouldering Club Tbilisi', '<p>Bouldering gym on Vera at the Mountaineering Federation.</p>\n', '<p>Vera Climbing Gym is a cozy bouldering facility with a height of 4.5 meters. Here, you will discover a variety of wall reliefs, numerous routes, and a friendly environment that will keep you motivated for climbing and training.</p>\n\n<p>Please note that there is no equipment available for rental in the gym, so you will need to bring your own gear.</p>\n', NULL, '<p>The gym is located in the building of the Chess Palace, on the first floor. Access is from the rear (parking) side. The address is 37-A Merab Kostava Street, Tbilisi.</p>\n', NULL, '', '<p>Oto -&nbsp;(+995)&nbsp;514 51 11 77</p>\n\n<p>Temo - (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:49:57', '2023-06-29 20:08:51'),
(220, 'us', 'S.K.Lucky', '<p>S.K. LUCKY Climbing Gym - one of the best gyms in Georgia. Here, you can enjoy bouldering and sport climbing routes.</p>\n', '<p>S.K. LUCKY Climbing Gym - one of the best gyms in Georgia. Here, you can enjoy bouldering and sport climbing routes. The walls for sport climbing reach a height of 12 meters, while the bouldering walls are 4 meters high. Instructors will be available in the facility to meet you and assist in choosing a route based on your experience and the level of difficulty. They will also provide insurance if you come alone and do not have a partner.</p>\n', '', '<p>The gym is located at Tbilisi University Street 6, Sports Complex Arena 2, on the second floor.&nbsp;You can reach the location by using public transportation or by driving your own car or taking a taxi (refer to the map for directions).</p>\n', '', '<p>The gym is equipped with all the necessary gear and equipment to ensure your comfort and enjoyment during the training sessions. Please be aware that equipment rental is subject to a fee.</p>\n', '<p>Tel: (+995) 574 80 95 02</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:52:39', '2023-11-20 01:38:14'),
(221, 'us', 'Vake Climbing Gym', '<p>The place for speed and sport climbing in Tbilisi.</p>\n', '<p>The wall has a height of 15 m, you can climb with quickdraws and top-rope aswell. For warming up, there is also a smaller bouldering wall. You can also find the world record wall for speed climbing here.</p>\n\n<p>A certain amount of climbing harnesses and quickdraws are provided in the gym. Anything else (e.g. climbing shoes) should be brought with you.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Opening hours&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Manday</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Tuesday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Wednesday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Thursday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Friday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Saturday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Sunday&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>10.00 - 22.00&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n', NULL, '<p>Sports Department, Chavchavadze Ave. 49. Easily reachable by bus (drop off at the bus stop in<br />\nfront of Vake Swimming Pool).</p>\n', NULL, '<p>The gym is equipped with all the necessary gear and equipment to ensure your comfort and enjoyment during the training sessions. Please be aware that equipment rental is subject to a fee.</p>\n', '<p>Tel: 571 22 05 04</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-02 18:54:34', '2025-01-22 18:45:28'),
(222, 'us', 'Ice Climbing In Gveleti (Kazbegi)', '<p>Ice climbing in Gveleti is one of the best places for this activity.</p>\n', '<p>Ice climbing in Gveleti is one of the best places for this activity. trad and dry tolling climbing in area is allowed.</p>\n\n<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_wUtCO6z1Xo\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer *; clipboard-write *; encrypted-media *; gyroscope *; picture-in-picture *; web-share *;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/V9XYJze\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '<p>From Tbilisi you need to drive to Kazbek &quot;Stepantsminda&quot; 160 km and then drive towards Vladikavkaz 9 km from Kazbek and turn left until you cross the bridge in Gveleti. Then go straight to the icefall. walking time 20/30 minutes depending on snow conditions.</p>\n', '<p>Best time for climbing is January,February &nbsp;and beginning of march if there is cold weather.</p>\n', '', '<p><strong>Guga -</strong>&nbsp;Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo</strong>&nbsp;- Mail; samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-19 20:23:10', '2025-01-21 00:35:13'),
(223, 'us', 'Ice Climbing In Ateni Valley', '<p>Ice climbing is a rather established sports discipline in Georgia. One of the best places to exercise is in Ateni Valley near the village of Biis.</p>\n', '<p>Ice climbing is a rather established sports discipline in Georgia. One of the best places to exercise is in Ateni Valley near the village of Biis.</p>\n\n<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DYw7XP9Iwv4\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"><iframe allow=\"accelerometer *; clipboard-write *; encrypted-media *; gyroscope *; picture-in-picture *; web-share *;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/dxgq6p1\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '<p>It will take about 1.5 hours from Tbilisi to Biys, the distance is 130 km. Following the main road, you turn left and enter the village. It is recommended to travel by 4&times;4 vehicle, as this way you will be able to drive another 300 meters into the village without leaving the car parked on the main road due to poor street conditions.</p>\n\n<p>After parking your car, you need to walk 20 minutes up the river until you reach a frozen waterfall 60 meters high and 5-15 meters wide.</p>\n\n<p>Nearest cities: 41&deg;51&#39;4&quot;N 43&deg;59&#39;6&quot;E ►</p>\n\n<p>Where to stay<br />\nThe place at the foot of the icefall is quite suitable for camping, but be aware that it is very cold at night!</p>\n', '<p>Depends on year temperature, February are the best months to go ice climbing.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>60M roupe (x2) or 120M (x1) (For top rope climbing)</li>\n	<li>Ice axe</li>\n	<li>Crampons</li>\n	<li>Harness</li>\n	<li>Helmet</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Crabin (x4-5)</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Fol lead</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>7-8 ice screws &amp;&nbsp;quickdraw</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p><strong>Guga -</strong>&nbsp;Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo</strong>&nbsp;- Mail; samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-19 20:47:03', '2023-08-08 22:49:54'),
(224, 'us', 'Slackline In Georgia', '<p>In Georgia, slackline is not the developed&nbsp;discipline, but it&#39;s&nbsp;developing.</p>\n', '<p><strong>Slacklining</strong>&nbsp;- refers to the act of walking or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balance_(ability)\">balancing</a>&nbsp;along a suspended length of flat&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Webbing\">webbing</a>&nbsp;that is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tension_(physics)\">tensioned</a>&nbsp;between two&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anchor_(climbing)\">anchors</a>. Slacklining is similar to slack rope walking and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tightrope_walking\">tightrope walking</a>. Slacklines differ from tightwires and tightropes in the type of material used and the amount of tension applied during use. Slacklines are tensioned significantly less than tightropes or tightwires in order to create a dynamic line which will stretch and bounce like a long and narrow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trampoline\">trampoline</a>. Tension can be adjusted to suit the user, and different webbing may be used in various circumstances. Slacklining is popular because of its simplicity and versatility; it can be used in various environments with few components.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Slacline in Georgia</strong> -&nbsp;In Georgia, slackline is not the developed&nbsp;discipline, but it&#39;s&nbsp;developing. Already in throughout Georgia are several highline regions(The most popular of them who is &#39;9 jvari&#39; in Racha).&nbsp;On the website <a href=\"https://slacklinegeorgia.wordpress.com/\">slacklinegeorgia.wordpress.com</a> you can find detailed information on all the regions of Georgia.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3>How to find us?</h3>\n\n<p><strong>I</strong>n <strong>Tbilisi</strong>, we gather most often in the &#39;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/eKc8QoHE9i62\">Vake park</a>&#39;, &#39;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/aZPtdvUCcf22\">Tbilis Botanical garden</a>&#39;(<a href=\"http://climbing.ge/outdoor/climbing_in_tbilisi\">in rock climbing area</a>)&nbsp;and the <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/y2o74pH4JtA2\">&#39;Lisi lake</a>&#39;. We inform each other about the meeting place on the facbook page &#39;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/1406012539710551/\">Sleckline Georgia</a>&#39;.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>I</strong>n <strong>Batumi</strong>, we gather most often in the &#39;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/qPTeY2Szba32\">6 May Park</a>&#39; and near &#39;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/1cRys9mKdMA2\">Tema Caffe Bar</a>&#39;. We inform each other about the meeting place on the facbook page &#39;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/372828259545512/\">Sleckline Batumi</a>&#39;.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>In <strong>Kutaisi,&nbsp;</strong>we gather most often in the &#39;<a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/oyKttSgyiRs\">Choma</a>&#39;(<a href=\"http://climbing.ge/outdoor/climbing_in_kutaisi\">in&nbsp;rock climbing area</a>). You can&nbsp;contact local guys&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/abuhdab\">Temo Kutdiani on facebook</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Info:</h3>\n\n<p>Facebook page:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/slacklinegeorgia\" target=\"_blank\">slackline georgia</a></p>\n\n<p>Tbilisi -&gt; Mail: Iraklisixarulidze@gmail.com; Facebook: <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/dusty.boots.7\">dusty boots</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Batumi -&gt; Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/erekle.chikvaidze?sk=wall&amp;fref=gs&amp;dti=372828259545512&amp;hc_location=group_dialog\">Erekle Chikvaidze</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Kutaisi -&gt; Facebook:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/abuhdab\">Temo Kutdiani</a>.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Guga -</strong>&nbsp;Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo</strong>&nbsp;- Mail; samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-03-19 21:01:44', '2024-04-15 20:34:50'),
(225, 'us', 'Javakhishvili clasic (3A)', '<p>AD, M1, 300M, 5A (3A - RUS)</p>\n', '<p>Climbing requires only three pitches and the difficulty of the route does not exceed 5A</p>\n', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"height:106px; width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pitch</td>\n			<td>Grade</td>\n			<td>Height</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P0</td>\n			<td>M1</td>\n			<td>100m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P1</td>\n			<td>5A</td>\n			<td>25m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P2</td>\n			<td>5A</td>\n			<td>50m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P3</td>\n			<td>4</td>\n			<td>50m</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>P0 - the route starts from the Leonidze-Javakhishvili couloir, from there we ascend to the saddle, where you will find a large boulder. To the left of the boulder you will see the assembled station.</p>\n\n<p>Р1 - from the station there are two options for ascent The first rope- from the station to the left, along the chimney, keep climbing to the right side - you&#39;ll stand on the shelf. Second option, there is a crack over the station, climb along the right side of the crack and go out onto the ledge.</p>\n\n<p>P2- from the station we go to the right along an inclined crevice and come out onto a thin rock with a positive slope. You can find it on the wall, continue climbing and find a station, assembled on three elements.</p>\n\n<p>Р3- from the station we continue the ascent and go out onto the ledge where we find the station on a boulder. From the station, go to the left along the path that takes us to the top of Javakhishvili. The classic route of Javakhishvili is the easiest route to the top of this mountain.</p>\n\n<p>The route is quite simple, so it is suitable for beginner climbers. For those who are just starting to climb the mountains.</p>\n\n<p>It takes 2-2.5 hours from the first camp to the base of the couloir. From the second camp 0.45-1.5 hours.</p>\n\n<p>The average time from the couloir to the summit is only 4-5 hours.</p>\n', NULL, '<p>The best time for the route is summer. At this time, the least precipitation falls, and the temperature is the highest (from 12 to 0 degrees), but you can go on the route in winter. Note: There is much more snow on the couloir in winter and avalanches are frequent. Temperature range from -15 to -25 degrees.</p>\n', '', '<p>Темо - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-10-03 07:01:13', '2024-05-06 01:48:07'),
(226, 'us', 'Climbing near Borjomi', '<p>Borjomi is located in Eastern Georgia. Here you can do rock climbing as well as various activities.</p>\n', '<p>Borjomi, located in Eastern Georgia, sits at an elevation of approximately 900 meters above sea level. The town has a population of around 10,000 people. Borjomi Municipality is highly popular among adventure tourism enthusiasts, offering activities such as trekking, cycling tours, rafting, and more.</p>\n', '<p>In the winter of 2021, the reabilitation of the region is&nbsp;began. Initially only 1 sector and 8 routes were done but already by the summer of 2022 it is planned to do more routes.</p>\n\n<p>Rock - basalt</p>\n', '<p>To reach Bakuriani from Borjomi, you&#39;ll travel approximately 9 kilometers until you reach the village of Tsaghveri. Once in Tsaghveri, head to the central square and make a left turn. Continue for 700-1000 meters towards the area of the village of Timote. On your right, you will come across a spring (marked with a sign). Adjacent to the spring, there is a bridge over the river. Cross the bridge to reach the rock. Parking is available at this location. For further details, please refer to the map.</p>\n', '<p>Best time to climb in the region: mid-spring to late autumn. The rock is mostly in the shade during the day so it is mostly cold during the day. We recommend that you check the weather before arriving in the region.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>60 m rope,</li>\n	<li>15 quickdraw,</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>Temo - Tel - (+995) 598457048.&nbsp;Email - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2021-11-21 18:30:47', '2023-11-20 01:45:06'),
(227, 'us', 'New climbing sectors near Borjomi', '<p>Borjomi municipality is one of the most popular among tourists and outdoor enthusiasts. A new climbing sector was recently added here.</p>\n', '<p>Borjomi is located 150 km from Tbilisi. Borjomi municipality is one of the most popular among tourists and outdoor enthusiasts. Here you can visit the Borjomi-Kharagauli National Park, where you can go trekking, visit sulfur baths and go rafting.</p>\n\n<p>20 km from Borjomi is the village of Tsemi, where one of the oldest climbing sectors in Georgia is located. Competitions were held back in the 80s of the 20th century. However, for the last 20 years, the region has been completely forgotten and no sporting events have been held here. There was no infrastructure in the sector, so it was impossible to climb here.</p>\n\n<p>In November 2021, work began on the renewal of the sector. At the first stage, only 3 routes were laid, but in the near future the work will be continued and even more traffic routes will be laid here.</p>\n\n<p>Follow the link to see a detailed description of the region.</p>\n', NULL, '<p><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/edit?mid=1zLk1GegB8K4QLJKiheI4D1odWy6rPffn&amp;ll=41.798991224962606%2C43.490982900000006&amp;z=18\">See the map to find out how to get to the region.</a></p>', NULL, NULL, '<p><strong>Temo -</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Tel:</strong> (+995) 598 45 70 48. <strong>Mail:</strong> samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>', NULL, NULL, '2021-11-23 17:24:11', '2024-08-12 14:23:58'),
(228, 'us', 'Climbing gym in Stepantsminda (Kazbegi)', '<p>.</p>', '<p>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-05-05 18:52:52', '2022-05-05 18:59:15'),
(229, 'us', 'Djavaxishhvili summit, \"Iliauni\" route', '<p>TD+/ED (5A RUS)</p>\n', '<p>In the morning, the route is in the sun, so it is pleasant to climb, both in summer and in winter.</p>\n\n<p>It will take you 2.5-3.0 hours to reach the base of the route from the first camp.</p>\n\n<p>1.0-1.5 hours from the second camp.</p>\n\n<p>The average time from the base of the route to the top is 4-6 hours.<br />\nIn the morning, the route is in the sun, so it is pleasant to climb, both in summer and in winter.</p>\n\n<p>It will take you 2.5-3.0 hours to reach the base of the route from the first camp.</p>\n\n<p>1.0-1.5 hours from the second camp.</p>\n\n<p>The average time from the base of the route to the top is 4-6 hours.</p>\n', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"height:106px; width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pitch</td>\n			<td>Grade</td>\n			<td>Height</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P0</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>30m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P1</td>\n			<td>5B</td>\n			<td>50m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P1.5</td>\n			<td>4</td>\n			<td>15m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P2</td>\n			<td>6A</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P3</td>\n			<td>5C+</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P4</td>\n			<td>5A</td>\n			<td>30m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P5</td>\n			<td>5b</td>\n			<td>30m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Top</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The route starts on the left of Leonidze-Javakhishvili culuar. We go up the steep slope to the bottom of the wall, we find a crack on the left side. This is where the route starts.</p>\n\n<p>P0 - we start climbing in a wide crack (for protection, use large-sized cams), we pass on a narrow taro and make protection on the chem. we continue climbing to the right. We go through a 4-5 meter wall to the big taro, go to the right and make a station on the big rock, at the foot of the big fireplace.</p>\n\n<p>P1 - We start climbing into the fireplace, there are many cracks on the right and left walls of the fireplace to make protection. Above the fireplace is a ceiling formed by the fall of large stones. On the left side, we find a narrow passage and go to the shelf. There is a chemical station near the gas station.</p>\n\n<p>P1.5 - walking simultaneously to the left of the station, we follow the shelf, climb a 5m high simple wall and find the base of the big wall on the existing taro.</p>\n\n<p>P2- we follow the groove in the middle of the big wall (the biggest groove), we follow the groove, on the right side we find a shelf and 4m above the shelf we find 2 palos on which we set up a station.</p>\n\n<p>P3 - We continue to climb in the groove until we come to a green wall with broken, broken rock. There are many narrow grooves on the wall. We continue to climb in the middle of the wall and find a narrow shelf where we make a station (making a station higher than this is not recommended).</p>\n\n<p>P4 - We continue to climb straight until we get to a large shelf below a large fireplace. We make a station at the foot of the fireplace.</p>\n\n<p>P5- We continue to climb the large chimney until we pass another large taro. From here we start walking simultaneously.</p>\n\n<p>TOP - from the shelf we continue to climb at the same time, on easy terrain. We go to the foot of the peak. We pass the peak on a small shelf from the west side (go to the left) and find a fireplace. As soon as we leave the fireplace, we find ourselves at the top.</p>\n\n<p>The average time from the base of the route to the top is 4-6 hours.</p>\n', NULL, '<p>The best time for the route is summer. At this time, the least precipitation falls, and the temperature is the highest (from 12 to 0 degrees), but you can go on the route in winter. Note: There is much more snow on the couloir in winter and avalanches are frequent. Temperature range from -15 to -25 degrees.</p>', '', '<p>Темо - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 19:24:25', '2024-05-05 23:29:42'),
(230, 'us', 'Leonidze Peak from South', '<p>EA - M1, 6A+, 350M (4A RUSS)</p>\n', '<p>The eastern wall of Javakhishvili is the most popular route of this peak. The route is good for the middle level climber.</p>\n', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"height:106px; width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pitch</td>\n			<td>Grade</td>\n			<td>Height</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P0</td>\n			<td>M1</td>\n			<td>200m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P1</td>\n			<td>6A+</td>\n			<td>50m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P2</td>\n			<td>6A</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P3</td>\n			<td>5B</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P4</td>\n			<td>4</td>\n			<td>100m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P5</td>\n			<td>5A</td>\n			<td>70m</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>P0 - The route starts from the Javakhishvili circus after widely dismissed couloir the path goes to the frozen and snowy slope. Exit to the saddle 200 m. near a big stone.</p>\n\n<p>P1 - On the right side from the saddle starts the wall with a phile, then continues to the little platform and the follow the narrow cleft with skates to the built station - 50 m.</p>\n\n<p>P2 - At the top of the station runs a small size cleft , after passing this cleft go to the left in the narrow Fireplace and the go to the big spread on platform, where is the station built on the skates. 5 m.</p>\n\n<p>P3 - On the right side from the platform goes in the simple Fireplace (50 m).</p>\n\n<p>P4 - Make a traverse of 100 m. on the right side to the wide platform from the head of the Fireplace. In the opened Fireplace to the peak direction ascend on the mountain range.</p>\n\n<p>P5 - Move to the right side from the mountain range to the peak.(70-80 m.)</p>\n\n<p>Descend with the same route</p>\n\n<p>Duration: 7-8 hours.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '<p>On the route you will need:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>X2 Rope 50 m</li>\n	<li>Stopers&nbsp;4-5&nbsp;(medium size)</li>\n	<li>Cams&nbsp;3-4 (medium-sized)</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Quickdraw&nbsp;4-5</li>\n	<li>3-4s carbine and self-defense</li>\n	<li>Belay device</li>\n	<li>Harness and helmet</li>\n	<li>Crampons and iceax (depending on the amount of snow on the couloir)</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>In winter, you will need additional equipment</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Snowsues</li>\n	<li>Ice screws 2-3</li>\n</ol>\n', '<p>.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 19:35:54', '2025-06-19 23:43:00'),
(231, 'us', '\"Didi digomi\"', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>First ascent - Bidzina Gujabidze and Alexandre Gujabidze</p>\n', '', NULL, NULL, '', '<p>.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 19:40:16', '2024-12-16 18:10:50'),
(232, 'us', 'Kameruni klasic (3A)', '<p>AD, M1, 600M, 5A (3A - RUS)</p>\n', '<p>The Cameroon classic route is one of the interesting and different routes in the Chauk massif. The route will be interesting for beginners and middle level climbers</p>\n', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"height:106px; width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pitch</td>\n			<td>Grade</td>\n			<td>Height</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P0</td>\n			<td>M2</td>\n			<td>500m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P1</td>\n			<td>5A</td>\n			<td>50m</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>P2</td>\n			<td>5B</td>\n			<td>40m</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>P0 - The route starts at the beginning of Asatiani - Camerooni couloir. We go up to the saddle with a long couloir (The average time of passing the couloir is 2-3 hours.) We start climbing on the left wall of the couloir.</p>\n\n<p>P1 - We start to climb the wall, gradually move to the left side. after 10m we find a old piton, from here we continue to the left again and enter the stone ridge where we find a anchor built on palos.</p>\n\n<p>P2 - We continue to climb up and pass the ridge. We cross to the left and at the highest point of the ridge we find a station built on a rock.</p>\n\n<p>TOP - We climb down from the anchor 8-9 meters down and find ourselves on the right platform (shelf). From here, we continue walking towards the peak. We pass the peak from the right side and climb to the top of the narrow flat surface (there is a tour at the top)</p>\n', '<p>.</p>', NULL, '', '<p>.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 19:45:32', '2024-05-06 01:49:41'),
(233, 'us', 'Asatiani Summit From South', '<p>D M1 5A 200M (4A; RUSS)</p>\n', '<p>.</p>\n', '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Pitch</td>\n			<td>Pitch Height</td>\n			<td>Inclination of<br />\n			the wall</td>\n			<td>Grade (UIAA)</td>\n			<td>Grade (ftr)</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R5</td>\n			<td>30</td>\n			<td>50</td>\n			<td>III</td>\n			<td>4-</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R4</td>\n			<td>20</td>\n			<td>10-20</td>\n			<td>II</td>\n			<td>4-</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R3</td>\n			<td>30</td>\n			<td>70</td>\n			<td>IV</td>\n			<td>4</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R2</td>\n			<td>40</td>\n			<td>60</td>\n			<td>III</td>\n			<td>4-</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>R1</td>\n			<td>40</td>\n			<td>70</td>\n			<td>IV</td>\n			<td>5</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>From the Javakhishvili circus ascend by the snowy couloir to the saddle&nbsp;(400 m). From the saddle climb on the third difficulty wall (50 m.) on the<br />\nright, the wall has cracks, sometimes you have to move on the simple climb ing philes. There is the station made up with pitons. Make 2-3 m. traverse on the right and get in the wide &ldquo;Fireplace&rdquo;. After 60 m. snowy and stone fallen &ldquo;Fireplace&rdquo; move on the less snowed saddle. At the end of wall side is built the station. on the left from the saddle move 40 m. on the narrow dismissed &ldquo;Fireplace&rdquo;. Ascend the long narrow platform and here is the station made up from the pitons. Make 20 m.</p>\n\n<p>traverse on the right to platform at the bottom of the little &ldquo;Fireplace&rdquo;. With the opened corner&rdquo;Fireplace&rdquo; move on the mountain range. Follow the dismissed mountain range to the peak.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Descend: With the same route. Duration: 8-9 hours.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '', '<p>.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 20:01:40', '2024-12-11 17:52:46');
INSERT INTO `locale_articles` (`id`, `locale`, `title`, `short_description`, `text`, `route`, `how_get`, `best_time`, `what_need`, `info`, `price_text`, `address`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(234, 'us', 'Myinvartsveri Clasic Route', '<p>PD (2A RUSS)</p>\n', '<p>The classic route to Mount Kazbek is the most popular ascent path to the summit, climbed by thousands of alpinists each year.</p>\n\n<p>While the route is technically quite straightforward, it requires good physical fitness and proper acclimatization.</p>\n\n<p>For acclimatization, it is recommended to rest for one full day at Bethlemi Hut. On the rest day, a light hike to the Bethlemi Church is advisable &mdash; both as a mild physical activity and an opportunity to enjoy the views and surroundings.</p>\n', '<p>The route begins at Bethlemi Hut (meteorological station). From there, we head north, following the slope alongside the glacier. Shortly after departing the Meteo Station, we pass by a campsite &mdash; the Cross Camp &mdash; which we bypass and continue heading north.</p>\n\n<p>After a short walk, we reach a section known as &ldquo;Khmaura&rdquo; (meaning &ldquo;noise&rdquo;), where frequent rockfall occurs. Therefore, wearing helmets is mandatory, and if necessary, crampons should be used. After passing through Khmaura, it is essential to rope up.</p>\n\n<p>Next, we reach the glacier plateau, from where we take a northeast direction and traverse the western slope. Due to numerous crevasses, roped travel is required, as well as the use of crampons, and, if necessary, ice axes.</p>\n\n<p>From the plateau, we ascend southward along a sloped section (incline approx. 25&ndash;35 degrees) and enter the saddle between the North and South summits.</p>\n\n<p>From this saddle, we continue northward along an icy slope (approx. 35&ndash;40 degrees) and reach the summit.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Departure from Meteo Station</strong>: 2:00 AM<br />\n<strong>Route duration (from Bethlemi Hut to the summit)</strong>: 8&ndash;10 hours<br />\n<strong>Descent</strong>: via the same route.</p>\n', NULL, '', '', '<p>.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-08-23 21:03:42', '2025-07-04 18:35:12'),
(236, 'us', 'Climbing in Gveleti', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Distance from Kazbek : 8 km (to Dariali Valley).&nbsp;The spot is under development with currently 2 sport climbing routes.&nbsp;Trad climbing possible.</p>\n', '', '', '<p>June-October but if good weather &nbsp;its possible to climb even in the winter.</p>\n', '<ol>\n	<li>60 m rope,</li>\n	<li>15 quickdraw,</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n', '', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 13:30:21', '2023-11-11 01:54:01'),
(237, 'us', 'Climbing Near Ananuri', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Climbing near Ananuri</p>\n', '<h2><strong>Area is not free for bolting !!!</strong></h2>\n\n<p>In case if you plan to come for bolting in Georgia please let local community to know about your plans. Any line which does not fit in our standards will be removed.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Dry tolling is not allowed&nbsp; in climbing area</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>camping is not allowed under climbing lines</strong>&nbsp; !!!!!!!</p>\n\n<p><strong>for your safety always use helmet&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;!!!!!!!!!</p>\n', '', '', '<ol>\n	<li>40 m rope</li>\n	<li>10&nbsp;quick draw</li>\n	<li>Helmet.</li>\n	<li>Harnes</li>\n	<li>Belay divice</li>\n	<li>Climbing Shous &amp;&nbsp;Chock bag</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p><strong>Guga -</strong>&nbsp;Mail: gugadabrunda@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Temo</strong>&nbsp;- Mail; samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Tel: (+995) 598 45 70 48</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 13:41:36', '2025-06-05 18:40:47'),
(238, 'us', 'Advanture 2022', '.', '<p><img alt=\"📢\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t39/1/16/1f4e2.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;16-17-18 სექტემბერი&nbsp;<img alt=\"📢\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t39/1/16/1f4e2.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🫵\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tc8/1/16/1faf5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მოდი ჭიათურის ტურისტულ ფესტივალზე და მოიწყვე დაუვიწყარი თავგადასავალი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🚀\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tc6/1/16/1f680.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;აღმოაჩინე სხვა ჭიათურა:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ქემფინგი/ Camping;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კლდეზე ცოცვა (მოყვარული) / Rock Climbing (amateur);<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კლდეზე ცოცვა (პროფესიონალი) / Rock Climbing (professional);<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჰაილაინი / Highline;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ნაოსნობა ტბაზე / Lake Boating;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სპელეოტურიზმი ძუძუანას და კოტიას მღვიმეში / Speleotourism in Dzudzuana and Kotika caves;<br />\r\n<img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />ველოშეჯიბრი მანდაეთში/Cycling competition in Mandaeti.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ფესტივალის განრიგი :</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურა</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕚\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t59/1/16/1f55a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;11:00 - პრეზენტაცია და პანელ - დისკუსია, ჭიათურის კულტურის სახლში.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - ტური &ldquo;ჯორჯიან მანგანეზის&rdquo; ტურისტულ პროექტში (საბაგირო, კორტი და სხვა).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - გალა კონცერტი Loud Speakers</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კაცხი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (მოყვარულები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სვერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (პროფესიონალები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 18:00 ჰაილაინის შოუ</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕚\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t59/1/16/1f55a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;11:00 - 17:00 ვია ფერატა ინფო ტური (​​მონაწილეები დაიყოფიან ოთხ ჯგუფად)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"👉\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/1f449.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;17 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სვერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 13:00 რეგისტრაცია კლდეზე ცოცვის შეჯიბრში (პროფესიონალები)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕐\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/ta8/1/16/1f550.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;13:00 - 18:00 შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ძუძუანას და კოტიას მღვიმე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;09:00 - 10:00 რეგისტრაცია ლაშქრობაში (მონაწილეები დაიყოფიან სამ ჯგუფად)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;კოტიას მღვიმე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - სპექტაკლი &ldquo;დოვინ დოვენ დოვლი&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"👉\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/1f449.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;18 სექტემბერი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მანდაეთის ტბა</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕙\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t31/1/16/1f559.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;10:00 ველო შეჯიბრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕛\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tda/1/16/1f55b.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;12:00 - 18:00 ნავებით შეჯიბრი ტბაზე</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"📍\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t2d/1/16/1f4cd.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურის ცენტრი</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🕘\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb0/1/16/1f558.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;21:00 - გალა კონცერტი Tamada</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🏕\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tdc/1/16/1f3d5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />16 სექტემბერს 10:00 საათზე გაიხსნება ქემფინგ ზონა ჩამოსული სტუმრებისთვის, რომელიც იფუნქციონირებს 18 სექტემბრის ჩათვლით.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🎶\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t1f/1/16/1f3b6.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;TAMADA და Loudspeakers</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🥪\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tfc/1/16/1f96a.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" /><img alt=\"🥤\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t4f/1/16/1f964.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;სთრით ფუდი და გამაგრილებელი სასმელები</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"💥\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t40/1/16/1f4a5.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურაში ამაღელვებელი, მომნუსხველი, გემრიელი და მისტიკით სავსე 3 დღე გელოდება.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"✔️\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t51/1/16/2714.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;ჭიათურის ტურისტული ფესტივალის გენერალური სპონსორია &quot;ჯორჯიან მანგანეზი&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🤝\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/t64/1/16/1f91d.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />პარტნიორები: ჭიათურის მუნიციპალიტეტის მერია, სვერის სათავგადასავლო ბანაკი და DMO იმერეთი.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"🔗\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tb3/1/16/1f517.png\" style=\"height:16px; width:16px\" />&nbsp;მხარდამჭერები: ტურიზმის ეროვნული ადმინისტრაცია.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Guga - ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(240, 'us', 'New climbing sector, near Ananuri', '<p>.</p>\n', '<p>Guga Dabrundashvili and Sopo Celidze boltid 3 new route near ananuri. Naw hear only 3 route but rock is big and poseble boltednew routes.</p>\n\n<p>For more information about sector location and routes see on this - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_near_Ananuri\">page</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Guga: Mail - gugadabrunda@gmail.com,&nbsp;Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:06:23', '2023-05-19 21:49:38'),
(241, 'us', 'New climbing routes, in Gveleti', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Guga Dabrundashvili boltid new sport climbing routes in Gveleti.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>More information about rocks see on this - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_in_Gveleti\">page</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Guga: Mail - gugadabrunda@gmail.com, Tel: (+995) 557 300 700.</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:16:02', '2022-09-05 16:23:23'),
(242, 'us', 'New, climbing sector, and 5 sport climbing route, near Borjomi', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Temo&nbsp;Samsonadze create new sector and bolted 5 new sport climbing route near Borjomi in village Mzetamze</p>\n\n<p>More information about this area see on this - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_near_Borjomi\">page</a>.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Temo - Tel - (+995) 598457048. Email - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:24:07', '2022-09-05 16:36:05'),
(243, 'us', 'New, sport climbing sector at the black sea cast.', '<p>.</p>', '<p>Temo Samsonadze boltid 3 new climbing line in Cixisdziri beach. Near Batumi.</p>\n\n<p>More information see on this - <a href=\"https://climbing.ge/outdoor/Climbing_At_The_Black_Sea_Coast\">page</a>.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Temo - Tel - (+995) 598457048. Email - samsonadze.temo9@gmail.com</p>', NULL, NULL, '2022-09-05 16:36:13', '2022-09-05 16:49:52'),
(244, 'us', 'Georgian mountaineers awarded by Golden Ice Axe', '<p>Georgian mountaineers awarded by Golden Ice Axe for ascending unclimbed Saraghrar peak in Pakistan</p>\n', '<p><em>Saraghrar Northwest, first ascent via the northwest face, 2,300m, ED2 or Russian/Caucasian 6B, 6b M5+ A3+ 80-90&deg;, from September 3-10, 2021. The route was descended with one further bivouac.</em></p>\n\n<p>The Saraghrar Massif, just south of the Afghan border in today&rsquo;s little visited Pakistan Hindu Kush, has several summits, but few climbers have ever reached them. Saraghrar Northwest (7,300m) remained unclimbed, despite prolonged and valiant attempts on the southwest buttress by three strong Spanish expeditions in the 1970s and early &lsquo;80s. The last of these topped out at around 7,150m on the northwest ridge, at a point they named Saraghrar Northwest II. Georgians Archil Badriashvili, Baqar Gelashvili, and Giorgi Tepnadze chose the previously unattempted northwest face, in its upper part a steep rock wall merging into the northwest ridge. They also opted to make the attempt in September, later in the year than normal, to lessen daytime heat and consequent rockfall.</p>\n\n<p>From a base camp at around 4,200m in the Rosh Gol, and with little pre-acclimatization, the three &ldquo;warmed up&rdquo; by making the first ascent of the south face and east ridge (1,800m, TD 60&deg;-ice 75&deg;-snow) of Languta-e-Barfi (6,833m), with one bivouac at 6,400m. This was the fourth ascent of the peak but the first from Pakistan.</p>\n\n<p>Around nine days later, on September 3, the Georgians began climbing the northwest face of Saraghrar Northwest at around 5,000m, continuing unroped up the huge snow and ice couloir that characterizes the lower half, to make a first bivouac at 6,200m. Above, a steep granite face formed the meat of the route.Overcoming hard mixed, free and aid climbing, they bivouacked at 6,400m, 6,600m, 6,750m, 6,850m, and ca 7,000m at the top of the face. Days five and six were spent on the difficult, vertical, 250m headwall, one pitch taking seven hours to lead.</p>\n\n<p>Above the top of the wall lay a long complex and corniced ridge with 300m of vertical gain. The three Georgians made their last bivouac near the exit to the Spanish route, and on their eighth day slogged up to the summit. The were able to reverse the route to the bivouac above the headwall on the same day, and next morning began rappelling the northwest face, continuing through the night until they reached the bottom.</p>\n\n<p>Info from -&nbsp;<a href=\"https://pioletsdor.net/index.php/en/home/2022-honoured-ascents/141-saraghrar-northwest-7-300m?mibextid=Zxz2cZ\" target=\"_blank\">pioletsdor.net</a></p>\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div data-oembed-url=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/ClLYMMXo6HS/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link\">\n<div style=\"max-width: 660px;\">\n<div style=\"left: 0; width: 100%; height: 0; position: relative; padding-bottom: 63%; padding-top: 284px;\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/QN2CKdu?app=1\" style=\"top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute; border: 0;\" tabindex=\"-1\"></iframe></div>\n</div>\n<script async=\"\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"//if-cdn.com/embed.js\"></script></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2022-11-20 10:22:07', '2023-08-02 16:20:31'),
(245, 'ka', 'ქვედა დაცვით ცოცვა', '<p>.</p>\n', '<h2>რჩევები ქვედა დაცვით ცოცვისთვის.</h2>\n\n<p>კარგი დამძღვევი უნდა იყოს ორიენტირებული მცოცავის უსაფრთხოებაზე. ამ სტატიაში თქვენ გაეცნუბით აუცილებელ უსაფრთხოების წესებს, რომელიც მოქმედებს ნებისმიერ აღჭურვილობასთან</p>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px\"><u><em><strong>ყურადღება</strong></em></u>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><u><em><strong>ყურადღებით წაიკითხეთ &nbsp;ტექნიკურ რჩევებში,&nbsp;რომელებიც&nbsp;მოცემულია ამ ინსტრუქცია, სანამ თავად გადაწყვეტ წვედა დაცვით ცოცვას და დაცვაზე დადგომას. თქვენ&nbsp; კარგათ უნდა გაიახროთ ქვედადაცვით ცოცვის ყველა მომენტი,</strong></em></u></li>\n	<li><u><em><strong>ამ უნარების დაუფლება მოითხოვს სპეციალურ მომზადებას. სასურველია გაესაუბროთ პროფესიონალ ალპინისტებს, რათა მათ დაადასტუროთ თქვენი ცოდნა, ან მოგცეთ რჩევები რომლებიც თქვენთვის გაურკვეველ მომენტებს გასაგებს გაახდის</strong></em></u></li>\n	<li><u><em><strong>აუცილებელია შეასღულოთ ტექნიკური&nbsp;უსაფრთხოების მოთხოვნები ნებისმიერ სიტუაციაში.</strong></em></u></li>\n	<li><u><em><strong>ეტაპობრივად გაეცანით ინსტრუქციას რათა რაიმე აუცილებელი ასპექტი არ გამოგრჩეთ. ჩვენ გთავაზობთ ძირითად ტექნიკის მაგალითებს. მაგრამ შესაძლებელია სიტუაციები რომლები აქ არ არის მოცემული.</strong></em></u></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h3><strong>1. პარტნიორის შემოწმება ასვლამდე (partner check).</strong></h3>\n\n<p>მარშრუტის არჩევის შემდეგ, მთამსვლელი ამოწმებს, რომ თოკის სიგრძე შეესაბამება ამ მარშრუტს ასევე თოკის ბოლოში კვანძს. ის ასევე ამოწმებს, რომ მთამსვლელის და დამზღვევის წონის სხვაობა არ არის გადაჭარბებული. ასვლამდე დამზღვევი და მთამსვლელი ამოწმებენ ერთმანეთის აღჭურვილობას.</p>\n\n<p>დამზღვევი ამოწმებს მცოცავის კვანძს და ქამარს, მცოცავი ამოწმებს დამზღვევის დაცვის სისტემას და დარაბინს.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Do a partner check before each climb.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8gAAA\" style=\"width:100%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>2. ცოცვის დაწყება პირველ წქსპრესში თოკის დაფიქსირებამდე.</strong></h3>\n\n<p>&quot;ტექნიკური დაცვა&quot; შეიძლება დაეხმაროს დაცემის შემსუბუქებაში პირველ რამდენიმე მეტრში, მანამ, სანამ მთამსვლელი პირველ ექსპრესში შეძლებს თოკის დაფიქსირებას. დამზღვევის მიზანი არ არის მცოცავის ხელით დაჭერა, მიზანია ცუდი დაცემის შედეგების თავიდან აცილება და დაცემის მართვა ისე, რომ მთამსვლელი სწორად დაეშვას კარგ ადგილას და არ გადატრიალდეს უკან, ანუ არ დაეცეს ზურგზე ან არ დახტეს განსაკუთრებით დიდი ქვაზე.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Spotting a climber before the first protection point.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8lAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<h3><strong>3. თოკის სწორი პოზიცია ექსპრესში</strong></h3>\n\n<p>სავალდებულოა მცოცავმა ექსპრესში თოკი სწორი მიმართულებით დააფიქსიროს (ჩააგდოს), რათა თავი აირიდოს თოკის ექსპრესიდან ამოვარდნისგან.</p>\n\n<p>აუცილებელია დაცვიდან მომავალი თოკის მხარე იმყოფებოდე ექსპრესსა და კლდეს შეორის ზოლო მცოცავის მზარე იყოს მიმართული ექსპრესიან მცოცავიკენ. ექსპრესის რბილი ბალდე არ უნდა იყოს დატრიალებული.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVCAA2\" style=\"width:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVHAA2\" style=\"width:20%\" /><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVbAAM\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVgAAM\" style=\"width:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVlAAM\" style=\"width:40%\" /><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVqAAM\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<h3><strong>4. დაცვის სისტემის გამოყენების უნივერსალური ტექნიკა</strong></h3>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Universal technique for correct use of a belay device.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8qAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>სურათზე მოცემული ხელების პოზიცია უნივერსალურია ყველა დასაზღვევი მოწყობილობისთვის GRIGRI, REVERSO თუ ATC სთვის. მარცხენა ხელი მოწყობილობიდან გამომავალ თოკზე უნდა გეჭიროთ ხოლო მარჯვენა მოწყობილობაში შემავალზე. <u><strong>მარჯვენა ხელის გაშვება კატეგორიულად აკრძალულია ნებისმიერ მოწყობილობაზე!!!</strong></u>&nbsp; იქნება ეს ავტომატური ჩამკეტი სისტემა როგორიც GRIGRI ან სხვა ნებისმიერი მოწყობილობა. თოკის მიწოდება ხდება მოწყობილობაში თოკის ნელი გასრიალებით, ისე რომ თოკის სიგრძე იყოს მცოცავის ასვლის სიმაღლის შესაბამისი. (მაგალითად: თუ მცოცავი ჯერ მხოლოდ პირველ ექსპრესთანაა, მიწიდან 2-3 მეტრში 5 მეტრი თოკის მიწოდება მოწყდომის შემთხვევაში მის დაცვას ვერ შეძლებს და იგი ძირს აღმოჩნდება. მადრამ როდესაც მცოცავი უკვე დიდი სიმაღლეზეა ასული, მაგალითად 10-15 მეტრზე მისთვის 5 მეტრი თუკის მიწოდება კრიტიკული არ იქნება.)</p>\n\n<p>დაცვის სისტემის გამოყენება ძალიან ფართო თემაა. გირჩევთ გამოყენებამდე გაეცნოთ კონკრეტულად იმ სისტემის გამოყენების ინსტრუქციას რომლის გამოყენებასაც გეგმავთ.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>5. სიფხიზლე, მოლოდინი და მობილურობა</strong></h3>\n\n<p>დამზღვევის როლი არ შემოიფარგლება მხოლოდ თოკის სწორი მიწოდებით. აუცილებელია მთამსვლელზე ფოკუსირება, დამზღვევს შეუძლია ამოიცნოს სტრესული მომენტები, რომლებისთვისაც ის შეძლებს რამდენი წამით უფრო ადრე მოემზადოს. კატეგორიულად აკრძალულია სიგარეტის მოწევა ან ტელეფონზე საუბარი, ასევე არასასურველია სხვა ადამიანებთან საუბარი. ასევე უნდა უსმინოთ მცოცავს შესაძლებელია მისთვის რთულ მომენტში მან თვითონ გაგაფრთხილოთ მოსალოდნელი ვარდნის შესახებ.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Vigilance, anticipation and mobility.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8vAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>6. მოწყდომის გაჩერება</strong></h3>\n\n<p>მცოცავის მოწყდომის შემთხვევაში ძლიერად დაიჭირეთ დამცავი მოწყობილობიდან გამომავალი თოკი,&nbsp; და ხელი ქვემოთ ჩამოწიეთ.არავითარ შემთხვევაში თოკს ხელი არ გაუშვათ. თოკის დაჭერა ზრდის ხახუნს მოწყობილობაში, რაც საშუალებას იძლევა მარტივად გააჩეროს თოკი მოწყობილობის შიგნით და შეაჩეროს მცოცავის ვარდნა.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Stopping a fall.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no90AAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>7. მცოცავთან კომუნიკაცია</strong></h3>\n\n<p>პარტნიორებს შორის კომუნიკაცია უზრუნვლყოფს ერთმანეთის ქმედებების უკეთ გაგებას რათა თავიდან ავირიდოთ რაიმე შეცდომა. ხანგრძლივი დისკუსიები არ არის ეფექტური, ჯობია წინასწარ შეთანხმებული ტერმინები გამოვიყენოთ, როგორიცაა &bdquo;დამსვი&ldquo;, &quot;ვწყდები&ldquo;, &bdquo;ვცოცავ&ldquo;, &bdquo;სადგური&ldquo;, &quot;თვითდაცვა&quot;, მეორე პარტნიორის მიერ ბრძანების გაგების შემთხვევაში აუცილებელი პასუხია &quot;გავიგე&quot;, ვერგაგების შემთხვევაში &quot;გაიმეორე&quot;. მოცემული ტერმინები მცირე ჩამონათვალია იმ ეფექტური საკომონიკაციო სიგნალებისა რომლებიც ცოცვაში იყენებენ. ასევე შეგიძლიათ შეუთანხმოთ თქვენ მეწყვილეს სხვა ბრძანებები რომლებიც თქვენთვის უფრო კომფორტული იქნება. მთავარი რიომ ერთი ბრძანება არ აღმატებოდეს ორ სიტყვას.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Communicating after a fall and before lowering\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no95AAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<h3><strong>8. დაშვება</strong></h3>\n\n<p>იმ შემთხვევაში თუ მცოცავმა დაამთავრა ასვლა ან აღარ სურს მარშრუტის გაგრძელება აუცილებელია აცნობოს დამზღვევს მისი გეგმის შესახებ ფრაზით &quot;დამსვი&quot;, დამზღვევი ამ დროს რაც შეიძლება მალე ჭიმავს თოკს ისე რომ მცოცავის წონა გადავიდეს თოკზე. ამის შემდეგ მცოცავმა უნდა აცნობოს დამზღვევს დასაშვებად მისი მზადყოფნის შესახებ სიტყვით &quot;დამიშვი&quot; ამის შემდეგ დამზღვევს შეუძლია ეგრევე დაიწყოს დაშვება ან თავიდან სიტყვით &quot;გიშვებ&quot; აცნობოს მცოცავს დაშვების დაწყების შესახებ რის შემდეგაც იწყებს დაშვებას.</p>\n\n<p>დაშვებისას დამზღვევი ვალდებული მივიდეს კედელთან (კლდესთან) რაც შეიძლება ახლოს, თუ ეს რელიეფის გამო შეუძლებელია დაიკავუს ისეთი პოზიცია რომ მცოცავის დაშვების მიმართულება არ ემთხვეოდეს გაჭიმული თოკს. დაშვება უნდა მიმდინარეობდეს სტაბილური მცოცავისთვის კომფორტული სიჩწარით. არ შეიძლება ზედმეტად სწრაფი დაშვება ეს განაპირობებს დაცვის სისტემის ზედმეტად გაცხელებას და თოკის გარე გარსის დაზიანებას.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Lowering\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no9AAAQ\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '', '', '', '<p><a href=\"https://www.petzl.com/INT/en/Sport/Good-practices-for-belaying-a-lead-climber?ActivityName=Rock-climbing\">მოცემული ინფორმაცია აღებულია PETZL-ის ოფიციალური საიტიდან</a></p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2023-04-13 18:41:54', '2023-11-21 03:25:56'),
(246, 'ru', 'Lead climbing', '<p>Lead climbing</p>\n', '<p>Lead climbing</p>\n', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, '2023-04-13 18:41:54', '2023-04-13 18:41:54'),
(247, 'us', 'Lead climbing', '<p>.</p>\n', '<h1>Good practices for belaying a lead climber</h1>\n\n<h2>A good belayer should be dedicated to the climber&#39;s safety. Here is a reminder of essential practices, valid with any equipment.</h2>\n\n<div style=\"background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px\"><u><em><strong>WARNINGS</strong></em></u>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><u><em><strong>Carefully read the Instructions for Use used in this technical advice before consulting the advice itself. You must have already read and understood the information in the Instructions for Use to be able to understand this supplementary information.</strong></em></u></li>\n	<li><u><em><strong>Mastering these techniques requires specific training. Work with a professional to confirm your ability to perform these techniques safely and independently before attempting them unsupervised.</strong></em></u></li>\n	<li><u><em><strong>We provide examples of techniques related to your activity. There may be others that we do not describe here.</strong></em></u></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h3><strong>1. Do a partner check before each climb.</strong></h3>\n\n<p>After choosing a route, the climber verifies that the rope length is suitable. He/she also verifies that the climber/belayer weight difference is not excessive. Before climbing, belayer and climber check each other&#39;s equipment setup: the partner check.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Do a partner check before each climb.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8gAAA\" style=\"width:100%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>2. Spotting a climber before the first protection point.</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Spotting can help reduce the consequences of a fall in the first few meters of a climb, before the climber has clipped the first protection point. Spotting is not about catching the climber, but helping avoid the consequences of a bad fall: it&#39;s about guiding the fall so that the climber lands correctly in a good location and does not flip over backwards.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Spotting a climber before the first protection point.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8lAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<h3><strong>3. Rope path</strong></h3>\n\n<p>The carabiner gate must always face away from the climber&rsquo;s direction of travel. The rope in the carabiner must pass through it from the cliff side to the outside. Incorrect positioning of the quickdraw or the rope could cause the rope to unclip, either due to rope movement or to the carabiner flipping on the bolt during a fall.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVCAA2\" style=\"width:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVHAA2\" style=\"width:40%\" /><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVbAAM\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVgAAM\" style=\"width:20%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVlAAM\" style=\"width:40%\" /><img alt=\"Rope behavior\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000002tMVqAAM\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<h3><strong>4. Universal technique for correct use of a belay device</strong></h3>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Universal technique for correct use of a belay device.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8qAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>This hand position is valid regardless of the device used: tube, GRIGRI, REVERSO...<br />\n<br />\nYour hand must never let go of the brake-side rope.</strong></p>\n\n<h3><strong>5. Vigilance, anticipation and mobility</strong></h3>\n\n<p>The belayer&#39;s role is not limited to giving slack quickly and at the right time. By staying focused on the climber, the belayer can recognize the stressful moments that require the greatest precision and responsiveness.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Vigilance, anticipation and mobility.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no8vAAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>When lead climbing above a quickdraw, make sure the rope is running to the side of your legs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Sport climbing rope around leg\" src=\"https://www.vdiffclimbing.com/wp-content/images/sport/sport-lead/sport-lead-6.png\" style=\"width:50%\" /></p>\n\n<p>If you fall with the rope around your leg, it can flip you upside down, causing you to hit your head on the wall and get &#39;rope burn&#39; behind your knee.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Climbing rope around leg\" src=\"https://www.vdiffclimbing.com/wp-content/images/sport/sport-lead/sport-lead-7.png\" style=\"width:50%\" /></p>\n\n<p>If you will be traversing far to the left after clipping a draw, it&rsquo;s better to orientate it so the rope-end gate faces right, and vice versa.<br />\n<br />\nIf the gate faces in the same direction as you, there is a greater (but still very small) chance of the gate opening in a fall.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Sport climbing quickdraw direction\" src=\"https://www.vdiffclimbing.com/wp-content/images/sport/sport-lead/sport-lead-14.png\" style=\"width:50%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"quickdraw length\" src=\"https://5cclimbers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/quickdraw-length.jpg.webp\" style=\"width:100%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"petzl quickdraw setup\" src=\"https://5cclimbers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/petzl-quickdraw-setup.jpg.webp\" style=\"width:100%\" /></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"quickdraw - incorrect carabiner orientation\" src=\"https://5cclimbers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Carabiner-direction-2.jpg.webp\" style=\"width:49%\" /><img alt=\"quickdraw - correct orientation of carabiner\" src=\"https://5cclimbers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Carabiner-direction.jpg.webp\" style=\"width:49%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"wrong orientation of quickdraw resulting in unclipping of quickdraw from bolt hanger\" src=\"https://5cclimbers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/1f167738-3929-437b-b49f-96a56eeb5c88_gatesopposed.1.gif.webp\" style=\"width:40%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>6. Stopping a fall</strong></h3>\n\n<p>In case of a fall, hold the brake-side rope firmly, while pulling it downward. Whatever the device used, the act of gripping the brake-side rope with your hand increases the rope friction in the device, allowing the fall to be stopped.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Stopping a fall.\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no90AAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>7. Communicating after a fall and before lowering</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Communication should allow the two partners to avoid being surprised by the movements of the other, to avoid any error. It&#39;s not effective to have long discussions, it&#39;s better to use terms agreed upon in advance, such as &quot;ok&quot;, &quot;go&quot;, &quot;take&quot;, &quot;climb&quot;...</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Communicating after a fall and before lowering\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no95AAA\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><strong>8. Lowering</strong></h3>\n\n<p>When the climber is ready to be lowered, after the agreed-upon signal, s/he is lowered on the rope and has no way of controlling the descent. All responsibility for this operation is on the belayer, who holds the climber&#39;s life in his hands.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Lowering\" src=\"https://www.petzl.com/sfc/servlet.shepherd/version/download/068w0000004no9AAAQ\" style=\"width:60%\" /></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '', '', '', '', '<p><a href=\"https://www.petzl.com/INT/en/Sport/Good-practices-for-belaying-a-lead-climber?ActivityName=Rock-climbing\">Tips by petzl</a></p>\n', NULL, NULL, '2023-04-13 18:41:54', '2023-11-29 07:10:15'),
